# Consolations
#
I'm sorry for your loss.
My condolences.
I'm here for you.
Words seem so feeble in moments like these.
Life is so precious, and death such a thief.
The depths of your pain I cannot comprehend, but I'll stand alongside you in the darkness, my friend.
My friend, I care.
#
# Grief
#
Grief is not an event. It is a process that does not end.
There is no end to grief. it is a labor we carry with us.
Working through death and loss takes work, not time. We must work to heal wounds. We must welcome our grief when we are able to sit with it.
Life is not comparative. It doesn't matter what loss we have experienced when we're helping other's process.
I am perhaps so full of grief that it leaks through the walls when the plaster dries.
So full of grief that the maintainers must be well fed at all times.
So full of grief the damn waits, ready to flood the artificial landscape below.
Grief is a part of life, and we will all know what it is to mourn at some point in our lives.
The Grieved are many, I am told, There is the various Cause. Death is but one and comes but once, And only nails the eyes.
A piercing Comfort it affords In passing Calvary.
How I suffered, dying a little each day until I got that fateful call.
So I'm still new at this, desperately trying to make sense of my life and her life now that she's gone.
grief suits me just fine in that it doesn't discriminate against me.
O' grief that which at times afflicts my very soul with sharp wounding sorrow.
How much more can my weary heart bear?
My life will never be the same.
Can't they just accept that I am grieving, let me mourn in peace and quit saying such hurtful things to me?
Back in 2004, I lost my girlfriend in a car accident.
I was shocked, devastated, and confused for many months.
I was 22 at the time and I never thought something like that could happen to me.
Before that, I was the confident guy, succeeding at most things I started.
Then, suddenly, my life was filled with darkness and my family and friends couldn't recognize me.
I tried hard to get out of that hole but apparently, I wasn't able.
That event changed me over the years and today.
It transformed me into who I am today, more humble and more grounded.
That being said, I wish you one thing: to spend quality time with people who are still in your life.
It is so heavy to carry.
This pathway through life Feels unbearable at times.
Forgive me if I cry, but there is nothing else to do.
Deep sadness overcame me When I heard the dreadful news.
