Freud's concept of the death drive, or Thanatos, suggests an inherent subconscious drive toward self-destruction and aggression.
He believed that this duality influences human behavior, including self-sabotage and the repetition of painful experiences.
Freud proposed the concept of the death and life drives in his work Beyond the Pleasure Principle in 1920.
The goal of all life is death.
Was 'death' a lacuna at the heart of Sigmund Freud's work?
Most of the time life appears so uncertain to me.
