The leading cause of death globally is ischaemic heart disease, which accounts for approximately 13% of all deaths.
In the United States, heart disease also ranks as the top cause of death, followed by cancer and accidents.
The Center for desease control and world health organization track death statistics.
The C.D.C. recently released updated official mortality data that showed 45,222 firearm-related deaths in the United States in 2020.
Firearm related deaths has overtaken motor vehical accidents as the leading cause of death for children and adolescents in the U.S.
